ProtoTheorem:
. "If $Ly=0$ is normal on $(a,b)$, then a set 
   $\{y_1,y_2,\dots,y_n\}$ of $n$ solutions of $Ly=0$ on 
   $(a,b)$ is a fundamental set if and only if it's linearly 
   independent on $(a,b)$."
